$232 million to the joint venture of KazMunaiGaz National Co.
and Citic Group to build a bitumen plant in Aktau, Kazakhstan.  TOO Caspi Bitum, as the venture between the Kazakh state
oil and gas company and Chinaâ€™s largest investment company is
known, plans to complete the 400,000-ton-a-year bitumen plant in
2012, KazMunaiGaz said in a e-mailed statement.  Bank of China will lend 80 percent of the project costs,
